Given, equal weights of ethane and hydrogen are mixed in an empty container at 25$$^\circ$$C.<br><br>Initial gram weight = $$\matrix{
   {_{wg}^{{C_2}{H_6}}} &amp; {_{wg}^{{H_2}}}  \cr 

 } $$<br><br>Number of moles = $$\matrix{
   {{w \over {30}}} &amp; {{w \over 2}}  \cr 

 } $$<br><br>According to Henry's law,<br><br>$${{{p_{{H_2}}}} \over {{p_{total}}}} = {\chi _{{H_2}}} = {{{n_{{H_2}}}} \over {{n_{{H_2}}} + {n_{{C_2}{H_6}}}}} = {{{w \over 2}} \over {{w \over 2} + {w \over {30}}}}$$<br><br>$${{{p_{{H_2}}}} \over {{p_{total}}}} = {{{w \over 2}} \over {{{15w + w} \over {30}}}} = {w \over 2} \times {{30} \over {16w}} = {{15} \over {16}}$$<br><br>So, the fraction of total pressure exerted by hydrogen is 15 : 16.
